# MARSYS Spren Licensing

This monorepo distributes code under two distinct licenses, depending on which
directory the code lives in. Read the per-package `LICENSE` file for the exact
terms that apply to a given component.

## Summary

| Component | Path | License | SPDX |
|-----------|------|---------|------|
| **marsys framework** (the multi-agent orchestration library, `pip install marsys`) | `packages/framework/` | Apache License, Version 2.0. Permissive license placing no restrictions on use, modification, or commercial distribution beyond attribution. | `Apache-2.0` |
| **Spren** (the personal AI assistant daemon) | `packages/spren/` | Functional Source License, Version 1.1, ALv2 Future License. Source-available with a 2-year non-compete that automatically converts to Apache 2.0. | `FSL-1.1-ALv2` |
| **Web frontend** (Vite + React visual builder) | `apps/web/` | Functional Source License, Version 1.1, ALv2 Future License | `FSL-1.1-ALv2` |
| **Desktop shell** (Tauri 2 wrapper) | `apps/desktop/` | Functional Source License, Version 1.1, ALv2 Future License | `FSL-1.1-ALv2` |
| **TUI client** (Textual terminal interface) | `apps/tui/` | Functional Source License, Version 1.1, ALv2 Future License | `FSL-1.1-ALv2` |

## Why two licenses

The marsys framework is a multi-agent orchestration library aimed at Python
developers. It is licensed under Apache 2.0, a permissive license that places
no restrictions on use, modification, or commercial distribution beyond
attribution.

Spren (the daemon, the visual builder, the desktop shell, and the TUI) is the
layered product on top of the framework. It is licensed under FSL-1.1-ALv2,
which is free and source-available for any non-competing use, including
individual use, internal company use, education, research, modification,
redistribution, and integrating into other software with attribution preserved.
The license forbids offering Spren as a competing commercial managed or hosted
service.

Each released version of FSL-1.1-ALv2 software automatically becomes available
under the Apache License, Version 2.0 on the second anniversary of its
publication. This means the current code becomes fully OSI-permissive over
time.

## Practical implications

| You want to... | Component | Permitted? |
|----------------|-----------|------------|
| Use marsys in your own software, even commercial | `packages/framework/` | Yes (Apache-2.0) |
| Build and sell a SaaS product on top of the marsys framework | `packages/framework/` | Yes (Apache-2.0); attribution required |
| Use Spren on your own laptop or inside your company | all of `packages/spren/`, `apps/*/` | Yes (Permitted Purpose under FSL) |
| Modify Spren's source for your own internal tooling | all of `packages/spren/`, `apps/*/` | Yes |
| Redistribute Spren modifications, with the FSL terms attached and copyright preserved | all of `packages/spren/`, `apps/*/` | Yes |
| Use Spren for non-commercial education or research | all of `packages/spren/`, `apps/*/` | Yes |
| Offer a hosted or managed Spren service that competes commercially with Marsys AI's Spren | all of `packages/spren/`, `apps/*/` | No, until each released version converts to Apache 2.0 (2 years after its release) |

## Where to find the canonical license texts

- `packages/framework/LICENSE`: Apache License, Version 2.0
- `packages/spren/LICENSE`: FSL-1.1-ALv2
- `apps/web/LICENSE`: FSL-1.1-ALv2
- `apps/desktop/LICENSE`: FSL-1.1-ALv2
- `apps/tui/LICENSE`: FSL-1.1-ALv2

